SIMPLE: radiometer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Radiometer
<hw>Ra`di*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧`d⟦icr⟧*⟦ocr⟧m"⟦esl⟧*t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>radius</ets> radius + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf.
F. <ets>radiom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A forestaff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument designed for
measuring the mechanical effect of radiant energy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It consists of a number of light disks, blackened on one
side, placed at the ends of extended arms, supported on a pivot in an
exhausted glass vessel. When exposed to rays of light or heat, the arms
rotate.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Radiometry</ent>⟦br⟧
